              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:ἁμαρτάνω&lt;SDBG:ἁμαρτάνω:000000&gt;} ‘to sin,’ {D:88.289}) a person who customarily sins</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>sinner</Gloss>
                <Gloss>outcast</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In contexts such as {S:04100201700046}, {S:04000901000026}, {S:04201500200024}, etc., ἁμαρτωλός may refer to persons who were irreligious in the sense of having no concern for observing the details of the Law. Such people were often treated as social outcasts.</Comments>
